dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.systemtemplate.transportprotocols

Interface ICanTpConnection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity, ITpConnection

    public interface ICanTpConnection
extends IEntity, ITpConnection
    ICanTpConnection: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    A connection identifies the sender and the receiver of this particular communication. The CanTp module routes a Pdu through this connection. atpVariation: Derived, because TpNode can vary.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

      • getPaddingActivation

        boolean getPaddingActivation()
        Query the value of the attribute PaddingActivation.

        This specifies wheter or not Sfs, FCs and the last CF shall be padded to 8 bytes length in case it contains less payload. true: The N-PDU received uses padding for SF, FC and the last CF. (N-PDU length is always 8 bytes) false: The N-PDU received does not use padding for SF, CF and the last CF. (N-PDU length is dynamic)

        Returns:
        The value or null

      • getMaxBlockSize

        long getMaxBlockSize()
        Query the value of the attribute MaxBlockSize.

        The maximum number of N-PDUs the CanTp receiver allows the sender to send, before waiting for an authorization to continue transmission of the following N-PDUs. For further details on this parameter value see ISO 15765-2 specification. Note: For reasons of buffer length, the CAN Transport Layer can adapt the BS value within the limit of this maximum BS

        Returns:
        The value or null
